  "body": "<!-- \r\nBy filing an Issue, you are expected to comply with the Code of Conduct, \r\nincluding treating everyone with respect:\r\nhttps://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md\r\n\r\nNot all sections will apply to all issue types.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen Teku runs as a Docker container, emoticons in the graffiti are not rendered.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n\r\nRun Teku via the following docker compose file\r\n\r\n```\r\nversion: '3.6'\r\n\r\nservices:\r\n  teku:\r\n    image: \"consensys/teku:22.5.2\"\r\n    user: \"1001\"\r\n    container_name: \"teku\"\r\n    restart: always\r\n    volumes: ['/data/teku:/data', '/etc/teku:/config', '/var/log/teku:/log']\r\n    ports: ['9000:9000']\r\n    command: --data-base-path=/data --validators-graffiti=\"Besu üêê Teku\" --network=ropsten --validator-keys=/config/keys:/config/secrets --ee-endpoint=http://10.0.0.1:8551 --ee-jwt-secret-file=/config/jwt-secret.hex --eth1-endpoint=http://10.0.0.1:8545 --validators-proposer-default-fee-recipient=0x... --logging=info --Xnetwork-total-terminal-difficulty-override=50000000000000000\r\n```\r\n\r\nwait for a block and check the graffiti, on Beaconcha.in it is rendered as `Besu ÔøΩÔøΩÔøΩÔøΩ Teku` instead of `Besu üêê Teku`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n\r\nSee the emoticons in the produced block\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\n\r\ninvalid chars are rendered in place of emoticons\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [How regularly does it occur?]\r\n\r\nalways when running in Docker\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: 22.5.2\r\n* OS Name & Version: Amazon Linux 2\r\n* Docker Version: 20.10.13\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: AWS",
