    "body": "There seems to be a mismatch between the charset the docker daemon is using and the charset that Teku is using.  The `String[] args` passed into our main method is already corrupted.\n\nSetting the `LANG` env var to match resolves the problem. For my Mac it needs to be set to C.UTF-8 - I suspect there are limited locales installed in the docker image.  So:\n\n```\ndocker run -e LANG=C.UTF-8 -it consensys/teku:develop --validators-graffiti=\"Besu üêê Teku\"\n```\n\nWorks. Whereas without the `-e LANG=C.UTF-8` it corrupts the unicode character. I'm not at all sure what should change.  By default we seem to be getting `POSIX` locale which uses US-ASCII.\nActually looks like openjdk defaults to C.UTF-8 these days (but we don't use their base image): https://github.com/docker-library/openjdk/issues/32\nSo adding `\"ENV LANG C.UTF-8` to our docker files is probably the right answer.",
